{{Quote|For years it has been sarcastically proclaimed that the principal export of the Neimoidian home planet is Brainworm Rot Type C. So many cases have been reported that, at the time of the writing of this guide, the Neimoidian home planet has been officially quarantined and is off limits to travelers.|Ebenn Q3 Baobab, ''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide''|<ref name="PhraseBook">[[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide (real-life book)|''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide'']]</ref>}}
'''Brainworm Rot Type C''' was one of the three variations of the [[Atmosphere/Legends|airborne]]<ref name="Phlegmpire" /> [[hive virus]]<ref name="Season1">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars – The Official Episode Guide: Season 1]]''</ref> [[Disease/Legends|disease]] known as the [[Brainrot Plague]] or the Brainworm Rot.<ref name="CSWE BrainrotPlague">{{CSWECite|I|90|Brainrot Plague (Loedorvian Brain Plague; Brainworm Rot)}}</ref> The disease targeted [[Cephalopod/Legends|cephalopods]] and [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoids]], affecting their [[Nervous system|central nervous system]] and causing nausea, sweating, impaired communication ability, and&mdash;if untreated by immunization&mdash;a swift [[Death/Legends|death]].<ref name="Phlegmpire" />

The [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidian]] [[Species/Legends|species]] served as a carrier of the virus, and by [[6 ABY/Legends|6 ABY]] it had been sarcastically claimed for [[Standard year/Legends|years]] that the disease was "principal export" of the Neimoidians' [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]],<ref name="PhraseBook" /> the [[Colonies/Legends|Colonies]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Neimoidia/Legends|Neimoidia]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> By that year, so many cases of Brainworm Rot Type C had been reported that Neimoidia had been placed under official quarantine, a fact noted in the 6 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]] edition of the [[Author/Legends|author]] [[Ebenn Q3 Baobab/Legends|Ebenn Q3 Baobab's]] [[Book/Legends|book]] the ''[[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide]]''.<ref name="PhraseBook" />

==Behind the scenes==
Brainworm Rot Type C was introduced in the [[2001]] book [[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide (real-life book)|''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide'']], authored by [[Ben Burtt]].<ref name="PhraseBook" />

